name: pandas-compat
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.1.1" %}
{% set name = "pandas-compat" %}
{% set sha256 = "67a707a22aca677c2e6f7d4aa17808e086b36d616341f146fcf33f8ee1059160" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 1
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - pandas

test:
  imports:
    - pandas_compat

about:
  home: https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas-compat
  license: BSD 3-clause
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'Pandas API compatibility layer'

  dev_url: https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas-compat

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jreback
